Subject: Can't install 'File System Scanning Proxy'
Description: I recently upgraded from v11.6 to v12 of the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor. Following the upgrade instructions, I tried to run the 'FS_UpdateProxy' instant job. It failed, almost instantly, with a weird 'key' error message. Following the manual update instructions, I uninstalled the proxy from my Proxy Servers. Unfortunately, I can't reinstall it. The installer gets to a screen that asks for my license, then says 'can't find license' and fails. I don't even see this within the installation instructions on Netwrix website. I am trying to install onto systems running Server Core (no UI), so even if I click 'browse', the installer crashes and I can't change the license path. What license do I use to run the installer? How do I pass that as a command line argument if I can't use the 'browse' button? Am I being asked for a license in error? Would there be a broken Registry entry, or similar, which is causing me to see this screen? The installer I'm running is: "auditor-enterprise-FileSystemProxy-12.0.0.1030.msi" Just in trying to troubleshoot by myself, I coped 'StealthAudit.lic' from my Enterprise Auditor installation directory so that it's in the same folder as the installer .msi. Unfortunately, since I uninstalled the old Proxy to upgrade, my proxies aren't functional now.
